\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\insrsid2049427 Psalm 69 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par O God, be attentive unto helping me; O Lord, make haste to help me. Let them be shamed and confounded that seek after my soul. 
\par 
\par Let them be turned back and brought to shame that desire evils against me. Let them be turned back straightway in shame that say unto me: Well done! Well done! 
\par 
\par Let them be glad and rejoice in Thee all that seek after Thee, O God, and let them that love Thy salvation say continually: The Lord be magnified. 
\par 
\par But as for me, I am poor and needy; O God come unto mine aid. 
\par 
\par My helper and my deliverer art Thou, O Lord; make no long tarrying.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\insrsid2049427 Psalm 142
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par O Lord, hear my prayer; give ear unto my supplication in Thy truth; hearken unto me in Thy righteousness. 
\par 
\par And enter not into judgment with Thy servant, for in Thy sight shall no man living be justified. 
\par 
\par For the enemy hath persecuted my soul; he hath humbled my life down to the earth. 
\par 
\par He hath sat me in darkness as those that have been long dead, and my spirit within me is become despondent; within me my heart is troubled. 
\par 
\par I remembered days of old, I meditated on all Thy works, I pondered on the creations of Thy hands. 
\par 
\par I stretched forth my hands unto Thee; my soul thirsteth after Thee like a waterless land. 
\par 
\par Quickly hear me, O Lord; my spirit hath fainted away. 
\par 
\par Turn not Thy face away from me, lest I be like unto them that go down into the pit. 
\par 
\par Cause me to hear Thy mercy in the morning; for in Thee have I put my hope. 
\par 
\par Cause me to know, O Lord, the way wherein I should walk; for unto Thee have I lifted up my soul. 
\par 
\par Rescue me from mine enemies, O Lord; unto Thee have I fled for refuge. 
\par 
\par Teach me to do Thy will, for Thou art my God. 
\par 
\par Thy good Spirit shall lead me in the land of uprightness; for Thy name's sake, O Lord, shalt Thou quicken me. 
\par 
\par In Thy righteousness shalt Thou bring my soul out of affliction, and in Thy mercy shalt Thou utterly destroy mine enemies. 
\par 
\par And Thou shalt cut off all them that afflict my soul, for I am Thy servant.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qc \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid10748004 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning32\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\cf6\insrsid2049427\charrsid10748004 \page }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\i\cf6\insrsid2049427\charrsid10748004 {\*\bkmkstart _Toc408568412}
The Doxology{\*\bkmkend _Toc408568412}
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  
\par Glory to God in the highest, and on earth, peace and good will among men.
\par 
\par  We praise Thee, we bless Thee, we worship Thee, we glorify Thee, we give thanks to  Thee for Thy great glory.
\par 
\par  O Lord, heavenly King, God the Father Almighty; O Lord, the only-begotten Son, Jesus Christ; and O Holy Spirit.
\par 
\par  O Lord God, Lamb of God, Son of the Father, that takest away the sin of the world; have mercy on us; Thou that takest away the sins of the world, receive our prayer; Thou that sittest at the right hand of the Father, have mercy on us.
\par 
\par  For Thou only art holy; Thou only art the Lord, O Jesus Christ, to the glory of God the Father.  Amen.
\par 
\par  Every night will I bless Thee, and I will praise Thy Name forever, yea, forever and forever.
\par 
\par  Lord, thou hast been our refuge in generation and generation.
\par 
\par  I said: O Lord, have mercy on me, heal my soul, for I have sinned against Thee.
\par 
\par  O Lord, unto Thee have I fled for refuge, teach me to do Thy will, for Thou art my God.
\par 
\par  For in Thee is the fountain of life, in Thy light shall we see light.
\par 
\par  O continue Thy mercy unto them that know Thee.
\par 
\par  Vouchsafe, O Lord, to keep us this night without sin.
\par 
\par  Blessed art Thou, O Lord, the God of our Fathers, and praised and glorified is Thy name unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par  Let Thy mercy, O Lord, be upon us, according as we have hoped in Thee.
\par 
\par  Blessed art Thou, O Lord, teach me Thy statutes.
\par 
\par  Blessed art Thou, O Master, give me understanding of Thy statutes.
\par 
\par  Blessed art Thou, O Holy One, enlighten me by Thy statutes.
\par 
\par  O Lord, Thy mercy endureth forever; disdain not the works of Thy hands.
\par 
\par  To Thee is due praise, to Thee is due a song, to Thee glory is due, to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qc \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid10748004 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning32\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\i\cf6\insrsid2049427\charrsid10748004 {\*\bkmkstart _Toc408568413}The Symbol Of Faith{\*\bkmkend _Toc408568413}
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par I believe in one God, the Father Almighty, Maker of heaven and the earth and of all things visible and invisible. And in one Lord Jesus Christ, the Son of Go
d, the Only-begotten, begotten of the Father before all ages; Light of Light, true God of true God; begotten, not made; of one essence with the Father, by Whom all things were made; Who for us men and for our salvation  came down from the heavens, and was
 
incarnate of the Holy Spirit and the Virgin Mary, and became man; And was crucified for us under Pontius Pilate, and suffered and was buried; And arose again on the third day according to the Scriptures; And ascended into the heavens, and sitteth at the r
i
ght hand of the Father; And shall come again, with glory, to judge both the living and the dead; Whose kingdom shall have no end. And in the Holy Spirit, the Lord, the Giver of life; Who proceedeth from the Father; Who with the Father and the Son together
 is worshipped and glorified; Who spake by the prophets. In One, Holy, Catholic, and Apostolic Church. I confess one baptism for the remission of sins. I look for the resurrection of the dead, And the life of the age to come. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2049427 At this point, a canon is read, being for the Theotokos, from the Oktoechos, or from the Menaion.
\par 
\par And after the canon, the Stichera from Vespers, or from the Praises of Matins if there be any appointed for the Saint.
\par 
\par Then: 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par It is truly meet to bless thee, the Theotokos, ever b
lessed and most blameless, and Mother of our God. More honorable than the Cherubim, and beyond compare more glorious than the Seraphim, who without corruption gavest birth to God the Word, the very Theotokos, thee do we magnify.
\par 
\par Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\f1\fs20\cf6\insrsid2049427 (Thrice)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par O Most Holy Trinity, have mercy on us. O Lord, blot out our sins. O Master, pardon our iniquities. O Holy One, visit and heal our infirmities for Thy name's sake. 
\par 
\par Lord have mercy. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2049427 (Thrice)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par Our Father, Who art in the Heavens, hallowed by Thy Name. Thy Kingdom come, Thy will be done, on earth as it is in Heaven. Give us this day our daily bread, and forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors. And lead us not into temptation, but deliver 
us from the evil one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid2049427 PRIEST: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427   }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs34 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs23\b\f1\fs34\insrsid2049427 
For Thine is the Kingdom, and the power, and the glory, of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  
\par 
