\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par Save, O Lord, Thy people, and bless Thine inheritance; grant Thou unto Orthodox Christians victory over enemies; and by the power of Thy Cross do Thou preserve Thy commonwealth.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2049427 Then, Sunday night through Thursday night (if simple service):}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par 
\par O God of our fathers, Who ever dealest by us according to Thy kindness, do not withdraw Thy mercy from us, but through their intercessions guide our life in peace. 
\par 
\par Adorned in the blood of Thy martyrs throughout all the world, as in purple and fine linen, Thy Church, through them, doth cry unto Thee, O Christ God: Send down Thy compassions upon Thy people; grant to Thy community, and to our souls great mercy. 
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.
\par 
\par With the saints give rest, O Christ, to the souls of Thy servants, where there is neither sickness, nor sorrow, nor sighing, but life everlasting. 
\par 
\par Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par Through the intercessions, O Lord, of all the saints and the Theotokos, grant us Thy peace, and have mercy on us, as Thou alone art compassionate. 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\insrsid2049427 On Friday night: 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par O Apostles, Martyrs, and Prophets, Venerable and Righteous Ones; ye that have accomplished a good labor and kept the Faith, that have boldness before the Savior; O Good Ones, intercede for us, we pray, that our souls be saved.
\par 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit. 
\par 
\par With the saints give rest, O Christ, to the souls of Thy servants, where there is neither sickness, nor sorrow, nor sighing, but life everlasting.
\par 
\par Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par To Thee, O Lord, the Planter of creation, the world doth offer the God-bearing martyrs as the first-fruits of nature. By their intercessions preserve Thy Church, Thy commonwealth, in profound peace, through the Theotokos, O Greatly-merciful One. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2049427 The troparion for a church patron saint is not said on Saturdays. 
\par 
\par On Saturday at Compline, the troparion and Kontakion of the Resurrection in the occurring tone are read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\page }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Troparion of the Resurrection. First Tone.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par When the stone had 
been sealed by the Jews, and the soldiers where guarding Thine immaculate Body, Thou didst rise on the third day, O Savior, granting life unto the world. Wherefore, the Hosts of the Heavens cried out to Thee, O Life-giver: Glory to Thy Resurrection, O Chr
ist. Glory to Thy kingdom. Glory to Thy dispensation, O only Lover of mankind.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
