\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par Thou didst arise from the tomb, O omnipotent Savior, and Hades was terrified on beholding the wonder; and the dead arose, and creation at the sight thereof rejoiceth with Thee. And Adam also is joyful, and world, O my Savior, praiseth Thee for ever.

\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Troparion of the Resurrection. Third Tone.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par Let the heavens be glad; let earthly things rejoice; for the Lord hath wrought might with His arm. He hath trampled down death by death; the first-born of the dead hath He become. Fro
m the belly of Hades hath He delivered us and hath granted to the world great mercy.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Kontakion of the Resurrection. Third Tone.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par Thou didst rise today from the tomb, O Merciful One, and didst lead us out of the gates of death. Today Adam danceth and Eve rejoiceth; and together with them both the Prophets and Patriarchs unceasingly praise the divine might of Thine authority.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Troparion of the Resurrection. Fourth Tone.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427  
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par Having learned the joyful proclamation of the Resurrection from the angel, and having c
ast off the ancestral condemnation, the women disciples of the Lord spake to the apostles exultantly: Death is despoiled and Christ God is risen, granting to the world great mercy. 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Kontakion of the Resurrection. Fourth Tone.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427  
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par My Savior and Redeemer hath, as God, raised up the earthborn from the grave and from their fetters, and He hath broken the gates of Hades, and, Master, hath risen on the third day.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Troparion of the Resurrection. Fifth Tone.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par Let us, O faithful, praise and
 worship the Word Who is co-unorignate with the Father and the Spirit, and Who was born of the Virgin for our salvation; for He was pleased to ascend the Cross in the flesh and to endure death, and to raise the dead by His glorious Resurrection
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Kontakion of the Resurrection. Fifth Tone.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427  
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par Unto Hades, O my Savior, didst Thou descend, and having broken its gates as One omnipotent, Thou, as Creator, didst raise up the dead together with Thyself. And Thou didst break the sting of death, and didst deliver Adam 
from the curse, O Lover of mankind. Wherefore, we all cry unto Thee: Save us, O Lord.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\page }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Troparion of the Resurrection. Sixth Tone.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427  
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par Angelic Hosts were above Thy tomb, and they that guarded Thee became as dead. And Mary stood by the grave seeking Thine imm
aculate Body. Thou didst despoil Hades and wast not tempted by it. Thou didst meet the Virgin and didst grant us life. O Thou Who didst rise from the dead, O Lord, glory be to Thee.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Kontakion of the Resurrection. Sixth Tone.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par Having by His life-bestowing hand raised up all the dead out of the dark abysses, Christ God, the Giver of Life, hath bestowed the Resurrection upon the fallen human race; for He is the Savior of all, the Resurrection, and the Life, and the God of all.

\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Troparion of the Resurrection. Seventh Tone.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427  
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par Thou didst destroy death by Thy Cross, Thou didst open Paradise to the thief. Thou didst change the lamentation of the Myrrh-bearers, and Thou didst command Thine Apostles to proclaim that Thou didst arise, O Christ God, and grantest to the
 world great mercy. 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Kontakion of the Resurrection. Seventh Tone.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par No longer will the dominion of death be able to keep men captive; for Christ hath descended, demolishing and destroying the powers thereof. Hades is bound; the Prophets rejoice with one vo
ice, saying: A Savior hath come for them that have faith. Come forth, ye faithful, for the Resurrection.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Troparion of the Resurrection. Eighth Tone.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par From on high didst Thou descend, O Compassionate One; to burial of three days hast Thou submitted that Thou mightest free us from our passions. O our Life and Resurrection, O Lord, glory be to Thee. 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\page }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Kontakion of the Resurrection. Eighth Tone.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
