Here the Order of Small Compline}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2901317  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2901317\charrsid2901317 is resumed."}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2901317 

\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2901317 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\b\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2049427 And these Troparia, 6th Tone:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\f1\fs20\cf6\insrsid2049427 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2049427 Have mercy on us, O Lord, have mercy on us; / for at a loss for any defense, / this prayer do we sinners offer unto Thee as Master; // have mercy on us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2049427 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2049427 Lord, ha
ve mercy on us; / for we have hoped in Thee, be not angry with us greatly,  / neither remember our iniquities; / but look upon us now as Thou art compassionate,  / and deliver us from our enemies, / for Thou art our God, and we, Thy people, // all are the
 works of Thy hands, and we call upon Thy name.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2049427 Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2049427 The door of compassion open unto us, O blessed Theotokos, / for, hoping in thee, let us not perish; / through thee may we be delivered from adversities, /
/ for thou art the salvation of the Christian race.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  
\par 
\par Lord, have mercy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\b\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2049427 . (Twelve Times)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Prayer I, of St. Macarius the Great.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427  
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par O Eternal God and King of all creation, Who hast vouchsafed me to arrive at this hour, forgive me the sins that I have co
mmitted this day in deed, word, and thought; and cleanse, O Lord, my lowly soul of all impurity of flesh and spirit, and grant me, O Lord, to pass the sleep of this night in peace; that, rising from my lowly bed, I may please Thy most holy name all the da
y
s of my life, and thwart the enemies, fleshly and bodiless, that war against me. And deliver me, O Lord, from vain thoughts and evil desires which defile me. For Thine is the kingdom, and the power, and the glory: of the Father, and of the Son, and of the
 Holy Spirit, now, and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Prayer II, of St. Antiochus:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par O Ruler of all, Word of the Father, O Jesus Christ, Thou Who art perfect: for the sake of the plenitude of Thy mercy, never depart from me, but always remain in me,
 Thy servant. O Jesus, Good Shepherd of Thy sheep, deliver me not over to the sedition of the serpent, and leave me not to the will of Satan, for the seed of corruption is in me. But do Thou, O Lord, worshipful God, Holy King, Jesus Christ, as I sleep, gu
a
rd me by the Unwaning Light, Thy Holy Spirit, by Whom Thou didst sanctify Thy disciples. O Lord, grant me, thine unworthy servant, Thy salvation upon my bed. Enlighten my mind with the light of understanding of Thy Holy Gospel; my soul, with the love of T
h
y Cross; my heart, with the purity of Thy word; my body, with Thy passionless passion. Keep my thoughts in Thy humility, and raise me up at the proper time for Thy glorification. For most glorified art Thou together with Thine unoriginate Father, and the 
Most Holy Spirit, unto the ages. Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid10748004 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Prayer III, to the Most Holy Spirit:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par O Lord, Heavenly King, Comforter, Spirit of Truth, show compassion and have mercy on me, Thy sinful servant, and loose me from mine unworthiness, and forgive all wherein I have si
nned against Thee today as a man, and not only as a man, but even worse than a beast, my sins voluntary and involuntary, known and unknown, whether from youth, and from evil suggestion, or whether from brazenness and despondency. 
\par 
\par If I have sworn by Thy name, 
\par 
\par or blasphemed it in my thoughts; 
\par 
\par or grieved anyone, 
\par 
\par or have become angry about anything; 
\par 
\par or have lied, or slept needlessly, 
\par 
\par or if a beggar hath come to me and I disdained him; 
\par 
\par or if I have grieved my brother, 
\par 
\par or have quarreled, 
\par 
\par or have condemned anyone; 
\par 
\par or if I have been boastful, 
\par 
\par or prideful, 
\par 
\par or angry; 
\par 
\par if, as I stood at prayer, my mind hath been distracted by the wiles of this world, 
\par 
\par or by thoughts of depravity; 
\par 
\par if I have overeaten, or have drunk excessively, 
\par 
\par or laughed frivolously; 
\par 
\par if I have thought evil, 
\par 
\par or have seen the beauty of another and been wounded thereby in my heart; 
\par 
\par if I have said improper things, 
\par 
\par or derided my brother's sin when mine own sins are countless; 
\par 
\par if I have been neglectful of prayer, 
\par 
\par or have done some other wrong that I cannot remember, for all of this and more than this have I done: 
\par 
\par have mercy, O Master my Creator, on me Thy downcast and unworthy servant, and loose me, and remit, and forgive me, for Thou art good and the Lover of mankind, so that, lustful, sinful, and wretched as I am, I may lie down and sleep and rest in peace. 

\par 
\par And I shall worship, and hymn, and glorify Thy most honorable name, together with the Father and His Only-begotten Son, now and ever, and unto the ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Prayer IV, of St. Macarius the Great}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par What shall I offer Thee, or what shall I give Thee, O greatly-gifted, immortal King, O compassionate Lord Who lovest mankind? 
\par 
\par For though I have been slothful in pleasing Thee, and have done nothing good, Thou hast led me to the close of this day that is past, establishing the conversion and salvation of my soul. 
\par 
\par Be merciful to me a sinner, bereft of every good deed, raise up my fallen soul which hath become defiled by countless sins, and take away from me every evil thought of this visible life. 
\par 
\par Forgive my sins, O Only Sinless One, in which I have sinned against Thee this day, known or unknown, in word, and deed, and thought and in all my senses. 
\par 
\par Do Thou Thyself protect and guard me from every opposing circumstance, by Thy Divine authority and power and inexpressible love for mankind. 
\par 
\par Blot out, O God, blo
t out the multitude of my sins. Be pleased, O Lord, to deliver me from the net of the Evil One, and save my passionate soul, and overshadow me with the light of Thy countenance when Thou shalt come in glory; and cause me, uncondemned now, to sleep a dream
less sleep, and keep Thy servant untroubled by thoughts, and drive away from me all satanic deeds; and enlighten for me the eyes of my heart with understanding, lest I sleep unto death. 
\par 
\par And send me an angel of peace, a guardian and guide of my soul and body, that he may deliver me from mine enemies; that, rising from my bed, I may offer Thee prayers of thanksgiving. 
\par 
\par Yea, O Lord, hearken unto me, Thy sinful and wretched servant, in confession and conscience; grant me, when I arise, to be instructed by Thy
 sayings; and through Thine angels cause demonic despondency to be driven far from me: that I may bless Thy holy name, and glorify and extol the most pure Theotokos Mary, whom Thou hast given to us sinners as a protectress, and accept her who prayeth for 
us. 
\par 
\par For I know that she exemplifieth Thy love for mankind and prayeth for us without ceasing. Through her protection, and the sign of the precious Cross, and for the sake of all Thy saints, preserve my wretched soul, O Jesus Christ our God: for holy art T
hou, and most glorious for ever. Amen.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Prayer V}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par O Lord our God, as Thou art good and the Lover of mankind, forgive me wherein I have sinned today in word, deed, and thought. Grant me peaceful and undisturbed sleep; send Thy guardian angel to protect and 
keep me from evil. For Thou art the Guardian of our souls and bodies, and unto Thee do we send up glory: to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Prayer VI}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par O Lord our God, in Whom we believe and Whose Name we invoke above every name, grant us, as we go to sleep, relaxation of soul and body, and keep us from all dreams, and dark pleasures; stop the onslaught of the passions and quench the burnings that arise 
in the flesh. Grant us to live chastely in deed and word, that we may obtain a virtuous life, and not fall away from Thy promised blessings; for blessed art Thou for ever. Amen.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Prayer VII, of St. John Chrysostom, according to the number of hours of day and night:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427  
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par O Lord, deprive me not of Thy heavenly good things. 
\par 
\par O Lord, deliver me from the eternal torments.
\par  
\par O Lord, if I have sinned in mind or thought, in word or deed, forgive me. 
\par 
\par O Lord, deliver me from all ignorance, forgetfulness, faint-heartedness, and stony insensibility. 
\par 
\par O Lord, deliver me from every temptation. 
\par 
\par O Lord, enlighten my heart which evil desire hath darkened. 
\par 
\par O Lord, as a man I have sinned, but do Thou, as the compassionate God, have mercy on me, seeing the infirmity of my soul. 
\par 
\par O Lord, send Thy grace to my help, that I may glorify Thy holy name. 
\par 
\par O Lord Jesus Christ, write me Thy servant in the Book of Life, and grant me a good end. 
\par 
\par O Lord my God, even though I have done nothing good in Thy sight, yet grant me by Thy grace to make a good beginning. 
\par 
\par O Lord, sprinkle into my heart the dew of Thy grace. 
\par 
\par O Lord of heaven and earth, remember me Thy sinful servant, shameful and unclean, in Thy kingdom. Amen.
\par 
\par O Lord, accept me in penitence. 
\par 
\par O Lord, forsake me not. O Lord, lead me not into temptation. 
\par 
\par O Lord, grant me good thoughts. 
\par 
\par O Lord, grant me tears, and remembrance of death, and compunction. 
\par 
\par O Lord, grant me the thought of confessing my sins. 
\par 
\par O Lord, grant me humility, chastity, and obedience.
\par  
\par O Lord, grant me patience, courage, and meekness. 
\par 
\par O Lord, implant in me the root of good, Thy fear in my heart. 
\par 
\par O Lord, vouchsafe me to love Thee with all my soul and thoughts, and in all things to do Thy will. 
\par 
\par O Lord, protect me from evil men, and demons, and passions, and from every other unseemly thing. 
\par 
\par O Lord, Thou knowest that Thou doest as Thou wilt: Thy will be done also in me a sinner; for blessed art Thou unto the ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Prayer VIII, to our Lord Jesus Christ}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par O Lord 
Jesus Christ, Son of God, for the sake of Thy most honorable Mother, and Thy bodiless angels, Thy Prophet and Forerunner and Baptist, the God-inspired apostles, the radiant and victorious martyrs, the holy and God-bearing fathers, and through the interces
s
ions of all the saints, deliver me from the besetting presence of the demons. Yea, my Lord and Creator, Who desirest not the death of the sinner, but rather that he be converted and live, grant conversion also to me, wretched and unworthy; rescue me from 
t
he mouth of the pernicious serpent, who is yawning to devour me and take me down to Hades alive. Yea, my Lord, my Comfort, Who for my miserable sake wast clothed in corruptible flesh, draw me out of misery, and grant comfort to my miserable soul. Implant 
in my heart to fulfill Thy commandments, and to forsake evil deeds, and to obtain Thy blessings; for in Thee, O Lord, have I hoped, save me.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Prayer IX, to the Most Holy Theotokos}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par O good Mother of the Good King, most pure and blessed Theotokos Mary, do thou pour out the mercy of thy Son and our God upon my passionate soul, and by thine intercessions guide me unto good works, that I may pass the remaining time of my life without ble
mish, and attain paradise through thee, O Virgin Theotokos, who alone art pure and blessed.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid2049427 Prayer X, to the Holy Guardian Angel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\insrsid2049427 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par O Angel of Christ, my holy guardian and protector of my soul and body, forgive me all wherein I have sinned this day, and deli
ver me from all opposing evil of mine enemy, lest I anger my God by any sin. Pray for me, a sinful and unworthy servant, that thou mayest show me forth worthy of the kindness and mercy of the All-holy Trinity, and of the Mother of my Lord Jesus Christ, an
d of all the saints. Amen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\f1\fs20\cf6\insrsid2049427 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\b\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2049427 Then, the Kontakion of the Theotokos:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par 
\par To Thee the Champion Leader, we thy servants dedicate a feast of victory and of thanksgiving, as ones rescued out of sufferings, O Theotokos; but as thou art one with might which is invincib
le, from all dangers that can be, do thou deliver us, that we may cry to thee: Rejoice, thou Bride unwedded!
\par 
\par Most glorious Ever-Virgin, Mother of Christ God, present our prayer to thy Son and our God, that through thee our souls may be saved
\par 
\par All my hope I place in thee, O Mother of God: keep me under thy protection.
\par 
\par O Virgin Theotokos, disdain not me a sinner, needing thy help and thy protection, and have mercy on me, for my soul hath hoped in thee.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\b\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2049427 Then the prayer of St. Joannicius:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\f1\fs20\cf6\insrsid2049427  
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par My hope is the Father, my refuge is the Son, my protection is the Holy Spirit: O Holy Trinity, glory to Thee.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qc \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid10748004 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning32\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\i\cf6\insrsid2049427\charrsid10748004 \page {\*\bkmkstart _Toc408568416}Here the Order of Small Compline is resumed.{\*\bkmkend _Toc408568416}

\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid2049427 PRIEST: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs34 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs23\b\f1\fs34\insrsid2049427 
GLORY TO THEE, O GOD, OUR HOPE, GLORY TO THEE}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 . 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\b\i\f1\fs20\cf15\insrsid2049427 CHANTERS:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2049427 
Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. Lord, have mercy, Lord, have mercy, Lord, have mercy.  Father }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\b\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2049427 (master)}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2049427 , bless.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid2049427 PRIEST: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427   }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs34 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs23\b\f1\fs34\insrsid2049427 
May Christ our God, through the intercessions of His most pure Mother, (the patron saint of the temple), and of all the saints, have mercy on us and save us, for He is good and the Lover of mankind.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\b\i\f1\fs20\cf15\insrsid2049427 CHANTERS:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2049427 Amen.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid2049427 PRIEST: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427   }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs34 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs23\b\f1\fs34\insrsid2049427 
Bless, (holy master and) holy fathers (mothers) and brethren, (sisters) and forgive me a sinner, all wherein I have sinned this day in deed, word, and through all my senses. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\b\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2049427 
\par And the brethren (sisters) (congregation) reply:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\f1\fs20\cf6\insrsid2049427 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par May God forgive and have mercy on thee, holy father.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\b\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2049427 And they make a bow (or a prostration, depending on the typicon), asking this forgiveness:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par 
\par Bless me, holy father, and forgive all wherein I have sinned this day in deed, word, and thought, and in all my senses, and pray for me a sinner.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid2049427 PRIEST: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs34 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs23\b\f1\fs34\insrsid2049427 
Through His grace may God forgive and have mercy on us all.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\b\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2049427 And he saith this Ectenia:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs34 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs23\b\f1\fs34\insrsid2049427 
Let us pray for the Orthodox episcopate of the Russian Church; for our lord the Very Most Reverend Metropolitan N., First Hierarch of the Russian Church Abroad; for our lord the Most Reverend }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2049427 (}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\b\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2049427 Archbishop or Bishop N., whose diocese it is}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\f1\fs20\cf6\insrsid2049427 )}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs34 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs23\b\f1\fs34\insrsid2049427  and all our brethren in Christ.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\b\i\f1\fs20\cf15\insrsid2049427 CHANTERS:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2049427 Lord, have mercy.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\b\i\f1\cf6\insrsid2049427 Quietly, slowly, and repeatedly, until the petitions are finished}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs34 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs23\b\f1\fs34\insrsid2049427 For the suffering Russian land and its Orthodox people both in the homeland and in the diaspora, and for the
ir salvation; for this land, its authorities and armed forces, and for every Christian land}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 . 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs34 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs23\b\f1\fs34\insrsid2049427 For them that hate us and them that love us. 
\par 
\par For them that are kind to us and them that serve us. 
\par 
\par For them that have asked us unworthy ones to pray for them.
\par 
\par For the deliverance of the imprisoned. 
\par 
\par For our fathers and brethren that have passed on before us. 
\par 
\par For those sailing upon the sea. 
\par 
\par For those bedridden in infirmities. 
\par 
\par Let us pray for the abundance of the fruits of the earth. 
\par 
\par And for every Orthodox Christian soul. 
\par 
\par Let us bless pious kings (rulers), Orthodox hierarchs, and the founders of this holy habitation.
\par 
\par Our parents, and all that have passed on before us, our fathers, brethren, and the Orthodox here and everywhere laid to rest. 
\par 
\par Let us say also for ourselves. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\b\i\f1\fs20\cf15\insrsid2049427 CHANTERS }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid2049427 Lord, have mercy}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\f1\fs20\cf6\insrsid2049427 (Thrice)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid2049427 PRIEST: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid2049427 
For the sake of the intercessions of Thy most pure Mother of (the patron saint of the temple), and all the saints, O Lord Jesus Christ our God, have mercy on us. 
\par 
